                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Hi,", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "I often happen to want to catch up with a mailing list, and thus\ndownload an archive, which I then subsequently merge into the current\nmailbox for that list.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Unfortunately, most mails, as archived by\nMailman's Pipermail at least, have this date format (example):", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Wed Jan 10 12:35:12 2007", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "while most mails which arrive through my mail server have this date\nformat:", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Mon, 09 Jun 2008 17:05:20 +0200", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Mutt can understand either of which fine if mails in one mailbox have\nonly one of these formats, but displays mails' dates in the index quite\nincorrectly when both formats are mixed in one mailbox.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "In that case,\nmails with the better format get their date shown correctly in the\nindex, but mails with the older format are displayed as being uniformly\nfrom \"Jan 01\".", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Threading and sorting seems to be unaffected, so it looks\nlike purely being a UI problem.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "It would be nice if mutt could either re-format the date headers on\nsaving the mails to a known-good format, or understand whatever date\nformat is present for all mails it reads, regardless of their origin,\nand even better if mutt could be instructed to behave either way.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Kind regards,", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "--Toni++", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
